Well. I like the Christmas Jesus best
and I'm saying grace.

231
00:14:30.120 --> 00:14:32.790
When you say grace. say it to
grownup Jesus. teenage Jesus...

232
00:14:32.956 --> 00:14:34.500
...bearded Jesus.
whoever you want.

233
00:14:34.666 --> 00:14:35.959
You know what I want?

234
00:14:36.126 --> 00:14:40.672
I want you to do this grace good.
so that God will let us win tomorrow.

235
00:14:41.131 --> 00:14:42.633
Dear tiny Jesus...

236
00:14:42.800 --> 00:14:47.638
...in your golden-fleece diapers. with
your tiny. little. fat. bailed-up fists...

237
00:14:47.888 --> 00:14:50.391
-...pawing at the air....
-He was a man. He had a beard.

238
00:14:50.557 --> 00:14:53.060
Look. I like the baby version the best.
do you hear me?

239
00:14:53.227 --> 00:14:55.020
I win the races and I get the money.

240
00:14:55.187 --> 00:14:58.732
Ricky. finish the damn grace.

241
00:14:58.899 --> 00:15:01.693
I like to picture Jesus
in a tuxedo T-shirt...

242
00:15:01.860 --> 00:15:04.571
...because it says. like.
"I wanna be formal...

243
00:15:04.738 --> 00:15:06.490
-Right.
-...but I'm here to party too."

244
00:15:06.657 --> 00:15:09.118
Because I like to party.
so I like my Jesus to party.

245
00:15:09.284 --> 00:15:12.830
I like to picture Jesus as a ninja
fighting off evil samurai.

246
00:15:12.996 --> 00:15:16.917
I like to think of Jesus.
like. with giant eagle's wings.

247
00:15:17.084 --> 00:15:20.170
And singing lead vocals
for Lynyrd Skynyrd...

248
00:15:20.337 --> 00:15:22.005
...with. like. a angel band.

249
00:15:22.172 --> 00:15:25.134
And I'm in the front row.
and I'm hammered drunk.

250
00:15:25.300 --> 00:15:26.927
Hey. Cal?
Why don't you just shut up?

251
00:15:27.094 --> 00:15:29.221
-Yes. ma'am.
-Okay.

252
00:15:29.388 --> 00:15:35.102
Dear 8-pound. 6-ounce.
newborn infant Jesus...

253
00:15:35.269 --> 00:15:37.062
...don't even know a word yet...

254
00:15:37.229 --> 00:15:41.859
...we just thank you for all the races
I've won and the 21.2 million dollars--

255
00:15:44.111 --> 00:15:45.612
Love that money!

256
00:15:45.779 --> 00:15:48.282
--that I have accrued
over this past season.

257
00:15:48.449 --> 00:15:50.576
Also. due to a binding
endorsement contract...

258
00:15:50.742 --> 00:15:53.287
...that stipulates I mention
Powerade at each grace...

259
00:15:53.454 --> 00:15:55.706
...I just wanna say that
Powerade is delicious...

260
00:15:55.873 --> 00:15:58.083
...and it cools you off
on a hot summer day.

261
00:15:58.250 --> 00:16:04.006
And we look forward to Powerade's
release of Mystic Mountain Blueberry.

262
00:16:04.173 --> 00:16:07.551
Thank you for all your power
and your grace. dear baby God. Amen.

263
00:16:07.718 --> 00:16:08.927
-Amen.
-Amen.

264
00:16:09.094 --> 00:16:10.387
Let's dig in!

265
00:16:10.554 --> 00:16:13.557
That was a hell of a grace. man.
You nailed that like a split hog!

266
00:16:13.724 --> 00:16:15.559
I'm not gonna lie to you. it felt good.

267
00:16:15.726 --> 00:16:17.436
Dad. you made that grace
your bitch.

268
00:16:17.603 --> 00:16:19.855
Hey. boys. I wanna see
some napkins in the lap.

269
00:16:20.147 --> 00:16:21.482
Boys. how was school today?

270
00:16:21.648 --> 00:16:24.902
I threw a bunch of Grandpa Chip's
war medals off the bridge.

271
00:16:25.569 --> 00:16:28.363
Sounds like a good day.
Texas Ranger. how about you?

272
00:16:28.530 --> 00:16:31.742
Well. the teacher asked me what
was the capital of North Carolina.

273
00:16:32.326 --> 00:16:35.162
-I said. "Washington. D.C."
-Bingo.

274
00:16:35.329 --> 00:16:38.832
She said. "No. you're wrong."
I said. "You got a lumpy butt."

275
00:16:38.999 --> 00:16:42.002
She got mad at me and yelled at me
and I pissed in my pants.

276
00:16:43.295 --> 00:16:45.547
I'm so proud of you boys.
You remind me of me...

277
00:16:45.714 --> 00:16:47.466
...precocious
and full of wonderment.

278
00:16:47.633 --> 00:16:49.259
I can't hold my tongue.

279
00:16:49.426 --> 00:16:52.429
These kids are my grandchildren.
and you are raising them wrong.

280
00:16:52.596 --> 00:16:54.014
They are terrible boys.

281
00:16:54.181 --> 00:16:56.850
Shut up. Chip.
or I'll go ape-shit on your ass!

282
00:16:57.017 --> 00:16:59.603
I'm gonna scissor-kick you
in the back of the head.

283
00:16:59.770 --> 00:17:01.688
-Yeah!
-Yeah. Turn up the heat.

284
00:17:01.855 --> 00:17:03.482
Go on and get some. boys.

285
00:17:03.649 --> 00:17:05.984
I'm 10 years old.
but I'll beat your ass.

286
00:17:06.151 --> 00:17:08.820
Chip. I'm gonna come at you
like a spider monkey.

287
00:17:08.987 --> 00:17:11.281
-Chip. you brought this on.
-What is wrong with you?

288
00:17:11.448 --> 00:17:13.742
Chip. I'm all jacked up
on Mountain Dew.

289
00:17:14.618 --> 00:17:15.619
I love that.

290
00:17:15.786 --> 00:17:19.289
You gonna let your sons talk to their
grandfather like that? I'm their elder.

291
00:17:19.456 --> 00:17:22.501
I sure as hell am. Chip.
I love the way they're talking to you.

292
00:17:22.668 --> 00:17:24.962
They're winners.
Winners get to do what they want.

293
00:17:25.128 --> 00:17:27.923
Only thing you ever done with your life
is make a hot daughter.

294
00:17:28.090 --> 00:17:29.341
We wanted us some wussies...

295
00:17:29.508 --> 00:17:32.302
...we would've named them Dr. Quinn
and Medicine Woman. okay?

296
00:17:32.469 --> 00:17:34.555
I work too hard for your bull. Chip.

297
00:17:34.721 --> 00:17:36.557
Come here.
You make me hot. Come here.

298
00:17:37.558 --> 00:17:38.976
Everyone just keep eating.

299
00:17:39.142 --> 00:17:41.728
-it's on.
-Come here. Come here.

300
00:17:43.981 --> 00:17:45.607
All right.

301
00:17:46.316 --> 00:17:48.235
I'll hold your hair.

302
00:18:00.581 --> 00:18:02.124
-Hey. Stephen.
-Hey. Ricky.

303
00:18:02.291 --> 00:18:04.251
Got those two tickets
for my special friend?

304
00:18:04.418 --> 00:18:08.171
Yeah. sure do. You know I do. Ricky.
Got them right here. buddy.

305
00:18:08.338 --> 00:18:10.507
Great. Hey.
how's your mama's hip?

306
00:18:10.674 --> 00:18:12.718
She's gonna be all right.
thank you for asking.

307
00:18:12.884 --> 00:18:14.970
-Appreciate it. Hey. good luck today.
-Thanks.

308
00:18:15.137 --> 00:18:17.556
That's the saddest thing
I've ever seen in my life.

309
00:18:17.723 --> 00:18:20.517
That boy leaves two tickets
for his daddy at every race...

310
00:18:20.684 --> 00:18:21.977
...and he never shows up.

311
00:18:22.144 --> 00:18:24.021
That's a shame.

312
00:18:24.187 --> 00:18:26.815
The human heart is such a mystery.

313
00:18:28.150 --> 00:18:30.527
As the laps wind down.
Jamie McMurray is the leader.

314
00:18:30.694 --> 00:18:33.739
Cal Naughton in second.
Ricky Bobby in third.

315
00:18:33.905 --> 00:18:36.533
What's up. Cal? You ready
for a little Shake-and-Bake-age?

316
00:18:36.700 --> 00:18:39.536
-Hey. buddy.
-Naughton Jr. is letting Ricky Bobby...

317
00:18:39.703 --> 00:18:43.332
...draft up to him to make
that slingshot move past McMurray.

318
00:18:43.498 --> 00:18:46.043
Can you believe that he would do that
for his teammate?

319
00:18:46.209 --> 00:18:47.878
Set him up that way?

320
00:18:48.962 --> 00:18:51.048
Slingshot. engage.

321
00:18:53.216 --> 00:18:55.093
And there goes Ricky Bobby
on the outside!

322
00:18:55.260 --> 00:18:56.470
That's how we do it.

323
00:18:56.637 --> 00:18:59.097
Makes his move.
Naughton's giving him plenty of room.

324
00:18:59.264 --> 00:19:01.892
What in the hell is he doing. guys?
Get him off of me.

325
00:19:02.059 --> 00:19:04.353
They touch! They spin!

326
00:19:04.895 --> 00:19:06.563
Snap!

327
00:19:08.106 --> 00:19:09.566
Come on. man!

328
00:19:13.695 --> 00:19:15.614
See you. wouldn't wanna be you.

329
00:19:26.625 --> 00:19:29.878
Look at that! Ricky Bobby's gonna
try to win the race in reverse.

330
00:19:30.045 --> 00:19:31.755
Man. he wants this win bad!

331
00:19:33.632 --> 00:19:35.634
Ricky Bobby wins it in reverse!

332
00:19:35.801 --> 00:19:37.678
Unbelievable!
l love that! That is cool!

333
00:19:37.844 --> 00:19:42.808
Jamie. losing's never fun. but here's
something to pick your spirits up.

334
00:19:42.974 --> 00:19:45.644
It's real nice.
I got it at Target. it's on sale.

335
00:19:51.274 --> 00:19:52.901
Yeah!

336
00:19:58.782 --> 00:20:01.952
-That's it. Another one. Another one.
-All right. man. We did it!

337
00:20:02.119 --> 00:20:05.622
I don't wanna be raining on
your parade. but I gotta tell you...

338
00:20:05.789 --> 00:20:09.918
...that was some of the dumbest
driving I have ever seen in my life.

339
00:20:10.085 --> 00:20:11.962
-Thank you.
-And I know you won the race...

340
00:20:12.129 --> 00:20:13.755
...but you're not gonna live forever.

341
00:20:13.922 --> 00:20:16.758
I'm not stupid. Lucius.
No one lives forever. No one.

342
00:20:16.925 --> 00:20:21.179
But with advances in modern science
and my high level of income...

343
00:20:21.346 --> 00:20:24.474
...I mean. it's not crazy to think
I can't live to be 245. maybe 300.

344
00:20:24.808 --> 00:20:27.352
-Ricky?
-Hey. Mr. Dennit.

345
00:20:27.519 --> 00:20:29.604
-Cheers.
-Yeah.

346
00:20:29.771 --> 00:20:32.107
-She already wasted?
-Celebrating.

347
00:20:32.274 --> 00:20:34.526
She's celebrating.
You feel pretty good today. huh?

348
00:20:34.693 --> 00:20:36.695
Look. Ricky.
early word out of NASCAR...

349
00:20:36.862 --> 00:20:39.656
...is your little obscene gesture's
gonna cost you 100 points.

350
00:20:39.823 --> 00:20:42.242
You know how much that costs us
in sponsorship dollars?

351
00:20:42.409 --> 00:20:44.161
With all due respect. Mr. Dennit...

352
00:20:44.327 --> 00:20:49.332
...I had no idea you had experimental
surgery to have your balls removed.

353
00:20:49.499 --> 00:20:51.543
What did you say?
What was that?

354
00:20:51.710 --> 00:20:53.587
Well. what?
I said. "With all due respect."

355
00:20:53.754 --> 00:20:56.506
That doesn't mean you get to say
whatever you wanna say to me.

356
00:20:56.673 --> 00:20:58.383
-It sure as heck does.
-No. it doesn't.

357
00:20:58.550 --> 00:21:00.260
it's in the Geneva Convention.
Look it up.

358
00:21:00.427 --> 00:21:02.596
I remember your daddy
used to love it.

359
00:21:02.763 --> 00:21:07.476
-This is not my dad-- This is my team--
-Used to love it when I used to win.

360
00:21:07.642 --> 00:21:10.061
Now. I suggest you and your wife.
Mrs. Jim Beam...

361
00:21:10.228 --> 00:21:12.397
...you guys go take a chill pill.
Enjoy the win!

362
00:21:12.564 --> 00:21:14.357
-Come on. man!
-Yeah. Ricky. Okay.

363
00:21:14.524 --> 00:21:16.234
Baby. photo op. photo op.
Come on.

364
00:21:16.401 --> 00:21:18.195
Come on. number one.

365
00:21:18.904 --> 00:21:20.989
Hold my hand. baby.

366
00:21:28.038 --> 00:21:32.000
Hey. Cal. I'm sorry
about wrecking you today.

367
00:21:32.167 --> 00:21:36.046
-I mean. but that was for the team.
-No. that's cool. That's cool. I know.

368
00:21:36.213 --> 00:21:38.715
I was thinking. though. one time...

369
00:21:38.882 --> 00:21:43.553
...it would be really awesome if. like.
you could slingshot me in for a win.

370
00:21:43.720 --> 00:21:46.348
Yeah. but-- Okay. but if you won...

371
00:21:46.515 --> 00:21:48.850
-...how am I gonna win?
-Yeah.

372
00:21:49.017 --> 00:21:51.603
-Think about it.
-No. I was thinking about it.

373
00:21:51.770 --> 00:21:53.897
I mean. it's not like
you're finishing 18th.

374
00:21:54.064 --> 00:21:57.150
-There's nothing wrong with silver.
-Nothing wrong with silver at all.

375
00:21:57.317 --> 00:21:59.611
I'm just kidding you. man.
I don't wanna win.

376
00:22:01.571 --> 00:22:03.448
I'll just bury it down inside.

377
00:22:03.615 --> 00:22:06.409
Bury it deep down in there.
and never bring it up again.

378
00:22:06.576 --> 00:22:08.745
It's painful. and I love you!

379
00:22:09.329 --> 00:22:13.416
So I was talking to Nana on Saturday.
and her birthday's coming up...

380
00:22:13.583 --> 00:22:16.127
...but I don't know what to get her.
She's gonna be 88.

381
00:22:16.294 --> 00:22:17.963
Get her a coffin.

382
00:22:22.092 --> 00:22:23.593
Don't stop.

383
00:22:30.475 --> 00:22:31.518
What is that?

384
00:22:31.685 --> 00:22:34.104
Someone made a tape of
something dying or something.

385
00:22:34.271 --> 00:22:36.273
Hey. turn that crap off.
What's going on?

386
00:22:36.439 --> 00:22:38.400
I want this music out of my head.

387
00:22:38.567 --> 00:22:40.068
Hey. turn that off!

388
00:22:40.777 --> 00:22:42.571
Turn that off right now!

389
00:22:48.201 --> 00:22:50.787
Why did you stop the jazz music?

390
00:22:52.497 --> 00:22:54.791
Was it not pleasant for you?

391
00:22:54.958 --> 00:22:57.836
No one plays jazz here
at The Pit Stop. okay?

392
00:22:58.003 --> 00:23:00.589
So why is the song on the jukebox?

393
00:23:00.755 --> 00:23:03.925
We keep it on there
for profiling purposes.

394
00:23:04.092 --> 00:23:07.220
We also got
the Pet Shop Boys and Seal.

395
00:23:07.888 --> 00:23:10.849
My name is Jean Girard...

396
00:23:11.141 --> 00:23:14.644
...and I am a racing-car driver
just like you...

397
00:23:14.811 --> 00:23:17.856
...except I am from Formula Un.

398
00:23:19.524 --> 00:23:22.444
I am the greatest one
in the whole world.

399
00:23:22.611 --> 00:23:28.158
I have been following your career
with great interest. Monsieur Bobby.

400
00:23:28.325 --> 00:23:30.744
I can't understand a word
you've said the whole time.

401
00:23:30.911 --> 00:23:32.746
Did you eat peanut butter
or something?

402
00:23:32.913 --> 00:23:35.916
You sound like a dog with peanut
butter on the roof of your mouth.

403
00:23:36.082 --> 00:23:39.669
I think what you are hearing
is my accent.

404
00:23:39.836 --> 00:23:42.422
I am French.

405
00:23:42.589 --> 00:23:44.215
You say you're French?

406
00:23:45.050 --> 00:23:48.219
We? No. we are not French.

407
00:23:48.553 --> 00:23:51.514
We're American.
because you're in America. okay?

408
00:23:51.681 --> 00:23:53.266
Greatest country on the planet.

409
00:23:53.433 --> 00:23:55.268
Well. what have you
given the world...

410
00:23:55.435 --> 00:23:59.606
...apart from George Bush. Cheerios.
and the ThighMaster'??

411
00:23:59.814 --> 00:24:01.691
-Chinese food?
-Chinese food.

412
00:24:01.858 --> 00:24:03.109
That's from China.

413
00:24:03.276 --> 00:24:05.445
-Pizza.
-Italy.

414
00:24:05.612 --> 00:24:08.198
-Chimichanga.
-Mexican.

415
00:24:08.365 --> 00:24:10.951
Really. smarty-pants?
What did French land give us?

416
00:24:11.117 --> 00:24:15.413
We invented democracy.
existentialism.

417
00:24:15.580 --> 00:24:17.499
...and the ménage à trois.

418
00:24:18.333 --> 00:24:20.543
-Those are three pretty good things.
-Hey.

419
00:24:20.710 --> 00:24:24.547
-Well. that last one's pretty cool.
-We created the missionary position.

420
00:24:24.714 --> 00:24:28.385
-You're welcome.
-Ricky Bobby...

421
00:24:28.551 --> 00:24:31.596
...I have come here to defeat you.

422
00:24:31.763 --> 00:24:34.599
Oh. well. there's strikes two and three
right there.

423
00:24:35.225 --> 00:24:36.851
Did you hear what he just said?

424
00:24:38.061 --> 00:24:40.355
Well. welcome to America. amigo.

425
00:24:45.568 --> 00:24:48.405
You are fast. Ricky Bobby...

426
00:24:49.114 --> 00:24:50.824
...but I am faster.

427
00:24:50.991 --> 00:24:54.744
All right. you let go of me.
you Formula One jazz nutjob!

428
00:24:54.911 --> 00:24:57.455
Like the frightened
baby chipmunk...

429
00:24:57.622 --> 00:25:00.458
...you are scared by anything
that is different.

430
00:25:00.625 --> 00:25:02.961
I will let you go. Ricky...

431
00:25:03.128 --> 00:25:07.424
...but first I want you to say:

432
00:25:08.883 --> 00:25:12.345
"l love crêpes."

433
00:25:12.971 --> 00:25:16.016
Don't you say it. Ricky.
These colors don't run.

434
00:25:16.182 --> 00:25:17.851
-I'm not gonna say it.
-Good.

435
00:25:18.018 --> 00:25:20.228
Hey. look. Frenchy.
I thought about it.

436
00:25:20.395 --> 00:25:22.647
So why don't you go ahead
and break my arm?

437
00:25:22.814 --> 00:25:25.942
I do not want to break your arm.
Monsieur Bobby...

438
00:25:26.109 --> 00:25:27.736
...but I am a man of my word.

439
00:25:27.902 --> 00:25:29.988
Here's the deal.
He's not gonna break it...

440
00:25:30.155 --> 00:25:32.615
...because I'm gonna slip
out of it right now. Houdini.

441
00:25:32.782 --> 00:25:34.075
Get down. you little pancake.

442
00:25:34.242 --> 00:25:35.827
Someone get me a beer
while I'm here.

443
00:25:35.994 --> 00:25:38.246
But you have forced me to do this.

444
00:25:38.413 --> 00:25:41.166
You are now mocking me
and making me look ridiculous.

445
00:25:41.332 --> 00:25:43.001
Just say. "l love crêpes."

446
00:25:43.168 --> 00:25:47.130
You know. just to put this in there. I had
e whole mess of crepes this morning.

447
00:25:47.297 --> 00:25:49.090
They're like pancakes.
maybe even better.

448
00:25:49.257 --> 00:25:52.010
-Are they the really thin pancakes?
-Yeah.

449
00:25:52.177 --> 00:25:55.221
They are the really thin pancakes.
It's just a French word for them.

450
00:25:55.388 --> 00:25:57.932
-My God. I love those.
-Put any syrups you wanton them.

451
00:25:58.391 --> 00:25:59.684
So. what if you just said:

452
00:25:59.851 --> 00:26:04.189
"l love really thin pancakes"'?
That is a fair compromise. no?

453
00:26:04.355 --> 00:26:06.524
-That is a fair compromise.
-Very fair. actually.

454
00:26:06.691 --> 00:26:09.444
No! Because then everyone
would know I really meant crêpes.

455
00:26:09.611 --> 00:26:12.781
-That's a pretty good compromise.
-Break it. Pepe Le Pew.

456
00:26:13.156 --> 00:26:14.407
As you wish.

457
00:26:17.535 --> 00:26:21.748
-He actually did it!
-All right. You did it. Back off.

458
00:26:21.956 --> 00:26:23.792
-I didn't say it!
-No. you did not.

459
00:26:23.958 --> 00:26:27.378
Your injury is one
of ignorance and pride.

460
00:26:29.631 --> 00:26:32.175
Hold it right there.
Mr. Fancy Pants Foreigner.

