691
00:40:11.619 --> 00:40:15.331
I'm saying. sometimes you get a knock
on the head. you get special powers.

692
00:40:15.497 --> 00:40:17.917
It happens all the time.
Read a comic book. okay?

693
00:40:18.083 --> 00:40:19.543
Everyone's real friendly.

694
00:40:19.710 --> 00:40:22.755
It doesn't hurt being Ricky Bobby.
I'm not gonna lie to you.

695
00:40:22.922 --> 00:40:24.590
So how's the physical therapy going?

696
00:40:24.757 --> 00:40:27.676
Oh. I gave that up.
Yeah. I gave that up...

697
00:40:27.843 --> 00:40:30.930
...after maybe the first day.
Within the first hour. I gave that up.

698
00:40:31.096 --> 00:40:33.182
I'm through lying to myself.
you know?

699
00:40:33.349 --> 00:40:36.810
It's time to be mature about this
and just face facts.

700
00:40:36.977 --> 00:40:39.438
I bought myself
a hundred-thousand-dollar...

701
00:40:39.605 --> 00:40:40.981
...handicap-accessible van...

702
00:40:41.148 --> 00:40:44.860
...with captain's chairs and the DVD
plasma screens in back for the kids.

703
00:40:45.027 --> 00:40:47.571
-You all paid up on that?
-Yeah. That's all paid in full.

704
00:40:47.738 --> 00:40:50.658
-it's parked out there.
-Hold on. man. Hold ....

705
00:40:51.158 --> 00:40:53.035
-We gotta tell him.
-Now?

706
00:40:53.202 --> 00:40:56.038
No. I don't care what the doctor said.
we gotta tell him now.

707
00:40:56.205 --> 00:40:57.790
Ricky. the doctor told us...

708
00:40:57.957 --> 00:41:00.751
...that we should let you work it out
in your own sweet time...

709
00:41:00.918 --> 00:41:02.294
...but. Ricky. you can walk.

710
00:41:02.461 --> 00:41:04.213
What did you just say?

711
00:41:04.380 --> 00:41:07.508
He's telling you the truth. man.
it's all in your head.

712
00:41:10.219 --> 00:41:13.263
You sick sons of bitches!

713
00:41:13.430 --> 00:41:15.265
I mean. you walk in that door...

714
00:41:15.432 --> 00:41:18.894
...on your two legs.
all fat and cocky...

715
00:41:19.061 --> 00:41:23.607
...and looking at me in my chair.
and you tell me it's all in my head?

716
00:41:23.774 --> 00:41:25.776
I hope that both of you have sons.

717
00:41:25.943 --> 00:41:30.948
Handsome. beautiful. articulate sons
who are talented and star athletes...

718
00:41:31.156 --> 00:41:32.992
...and they have their legs
taken away!

719
00:41:33.158 --> 00:41:35.119
I pray you know
that pain and that hurt.

720
00:41:35.327 --> 00:41:37.621
Don't you put that evil on me.
Ricky Bobby!

721
00:41:37.788 --> 00:41:42.209
Don't you put that on us!
You are not paralyzed!

722
00:41:42.376 --> 00:41:44.128
I am so paralyzed!

723
00:41:44.294 --> 00:41:47.756
-No. no. no! No. he needs to know!
-Getting a little rough on him.

724
00:41:47.923 --> 00:41:50.384
-He's always crying!
-Tough love. it is. Tough love.

725
00:41:50.551 --> 00:41:53.262
- Wake up. idiot!
-You wanna know what I am'?!

726
00:41:53.429 --> 00:41:55.889
You wanna see what my life is'?!

727
00:41:56.056 --> 00:41:57.307
Don't do it.

728
00:41:57.474 --> 00:42:01.687
-You wanna see what's going on here?
-Don't you stick that knife in your leg.

729
00:42:10.029 --> 00:42:12.740
-Man!
-Hold on. hold on.

730
00:42:13.949 --> 00:42:16.243
-Hold on. now. Walk it off.
-Oh. that hurts.

731
00:42:16.410 --> 00:42:17.745
-Oh. my--!
-Walk it off.

732
00:42:17.911 --> 00:42:19.747
Stretch. stretch. Stretch it out.

733
00:42:19.913 --> 00:42:22.416
Hey. man.
You can walk! You can walk!

734
00:42:22.583 --> 00:42:24.168
I can walk!

735
00:42:24.918 --> 00:42:27.254
-I think I touched a nerve.
-Right there.

736
00:42:27.421 --> 00:42:30.174
All right. we got it. we got it.
Hold it right there.

737
00:42:30.340 --> 00:42:31.675
Maybe don't touch it.

738
00:42:31.842 --> 00:42:33.802
-Can you feel it?
-I can!

739
00:42:33.969 --> 00:42:36.346
We'll use this knife to pry it out.
We'll pull it out.

740
00:42:36.513 --> 00:42:39.141
-Now we got two in there.
-Just don't think about it.

741
00:42:39.308 --> 00:42:41.602
-We're going down a bad path.
-Cut around the meat.

742
00:42:41.769 --> 00:42:43.479
I'll out right here. Stretch it out.

743
00:42:43.645 --> 00:42:45.981
Just take out e plug of meat.
Just like e deer.

744
00:42:46.148 --> 00:42:48.901
We gotta wiggle it a little bit. That's it.
Can you feel that?

745
00:42:49.068 --> 00:42:50.903
-Yeah. I feel that.
-You are back!

746
00:42:51.070 --> 00:42:52.696
I love you guys!

747
00:42:53.322 --> 00:42:56.992
Hey. I'm sorry. guys. I mean.
I hope your boys don't lose their legs.

748
00:42:57.159 --> 00:43:00.496
-Thanks. buddy.
-So when do I get to drive again?

749
00:43:00.662 --> 00:43:03.665
Well. that's the thing. The doctor
said you suffered major trauma...

750
00:43:03.832 --> 00:43:06.168
...and he thinks you should
take it slow for a while.

751
00:43:06.335 --> 00:43:10.130
Yeah. so. I was thinking. like.
while you're resting up and stuff...

752
00:43:10.297 --> 00:43:13.258
-...maybe you could let me win a few.
-Well. there you go.

753
00:43:13.425 --> 00:43:15.302
Yeah. that ain't gonna happen.

754
00:43:15.761 --> 00:43:18.722
Yeah. I'm Ricky Bobby.
I mean. you know how I play it.

755
00:43:18.889 --> 00:43:21.100
-Yeah.
-First or last. right. baby?

756
00:43:21.266 --> 00:43:23.685
-Don't know what I was thinking.
-Besides...

757
00:43:23.852 --> 00:43:26.730
...Dennit Jr. must be freaking out.
All the money he's losing?

758
00:43:26.897 --> 00:43:28.524
Without me on the track?

759
00:43:28.690 --> 00:43:29.900
I mean. I just laugh...

760
00:43:30.067 --> 00:43:33.028
...thinking about him whining
all the time. bitching and moaning:

761
00:43:33.195 --> 00:43:35.280
"Damn. I wish Ricky was here."

762
00:43:35.447 --> 00:43:36.990
You know what I mean?

763
00:43:40.828 --> 00:43:42.871
What?

764
00:43:43.038 --> 00:43:45.499
Frenchy can drive.

765
00:43:49.211 --> 00:43:50.629
Oh. no.

766
00:44:18.532 --> 00:44:20.284
Very good.

767
00:44:20.450 --> 00:44:22.619
C'est la vie and que sera. sera.

768
00:44:22.786 --> 00:44:25.831
It looks like the NASCAR
has gone French.

769
00:44:26.206 --> 00:44:27.749
Well. in other news. Ricky Bobby...

770
00:44:27.916 --> 00:44:31.044
...is going to be running some test
laps this weekend at Rockingham...

771
00:44:31.211 --> 00:44:33.505
...in an attempt to come back
from his grisly crash.

772
00:44:35.090 --> 00:44:37.134
It's one of the hardest things
to do in racing.

773
00:44:37.301 --> 00:44:40.012
To try to bounce back after
a devastating. violent wreck.

774
00:44:40.179 --> 00:44:42.639
Ricky Bobby was traumatized
during the incident.

775
00:44:42.806 --> 00:44:44.099
All right. baby. Come on. now.

776
00:44:44.266 --> 00:44:47.644
But today he gets to strap back into
a racecar for the first time since...

777
00:44:47.811 --> 00:44:49.980
...to try to show he can still
get the job done.

778
00:44:50.147 --> 00:44:53.442
-He's gonna be great. Yep.
-He's gonna be great. sure.

779
00:44:53.609 --> 00:44:56.361
Would you stop staring at me like that.
Susan? I swear...

780
00:44:56.528 --> 00:44:59.031
...you are the weirdest little girl
I've ever seen.

781
00:44:59.198 --> 00:45:01.950
Okay. I'm really gonna open it up!

782
00:45:05.078 --> 00:45:08.165
I missed you. Mama Speed.
Ricky Bobby's back.

783
00:45:08.332 --> 00:45:10.125
Wait. how fast is he going?

784
00:45:10.292 --> 00:45:11.877
Twenty-six miles an hour.

785
00:45:14.338 --> 00:45:17.716
What were those things?
Were those the other cars?

786
00:45:23.138 --> 00:45:25.641
Oh. God. So fast.

787
00:45:25.807 --> 00:45:27.601
Go. baby! There you are.

788
00:45:27.851 --> 00:45:29.561
Am I on fire? I'm on fire.

789
00:45:29.728 --> 00:45:31.730
-No. no. you're not on fire.
-Stretch it out.

790
00:45:31.897 --> 00:45:33.523
-it's okay. baby.
-Take it easy.

791
00:45:35.108 --> 00:45:37.778
-Oh. God. I'm gonna get sick.
-Oh. God.

792
00:45:37.986 --> 00:45:41.823
-Oh. he's in his underwear again.
-Ricky! Please put your clothes on.

793
00:45:41.990 --> 00:45:44.284
He's in his underwear again.
Go get him. fellas.

794
00:45:44.451 --> 00:45:45.702
Oh. Lord.

795
00:45:45.869 --> 00:45:48.747
You know who's gonna be
number one at Dennit Racing?

796
00:45:49.498 --> 00:45:52.251
-Not Ricky?
-I'm gonna windmill you.

797
00:45:52.417 --> 00:45:55.337
Mr. Cal Naughton Jr.

798
00:45:55.504 --> 00:45:58.131
-Come back at him. it's the only way.
-Who are you?

799
00:45:58.298 --> 00:45:59.967
-Number one.
-No.

800
00:46:00.133 --> 00:46:03.679
-Oh. yes. ma'am.
-Ricky! Come on. man!

801
00:46:03.845 --> 00:46:05.222
It's embarrassing.

802
00:46:05.389 --> 00:46:09.268
The ninjas are trying to get me.
The ninjas are trying to get me.

803
00:46:09.434 --> 00:46:11.186
-Oh. my God.
-What happened?

804
00:46:11.353 --> 00:46:13.814
What happened? He's done.
He's done.

805
00:46:13.981 --> 00:46:16.525
That's what's happened.
it's over. He's finished.

806
00:46:16.775 --> 00:46:18.360
What's gonna happen to me?

807
00:46:18.527 --> 00:46:21.530
I feel like I was riding inside
an asteroid or a comet or something.

808
00:46:21.697 --> 00:46:23.740
Yeah. you were going fast.

809
00:46:23.907 --> 00:46:26.034
-Look at that.
-What are we gonna do?

810
00:46:26.201 --> 00:46:28.787
This is ugly.
This is bad for all of us. Look at that.

811
00:46:28.954 --> 00:46:31.915
-I gotta go check on cuckoo bird.
-No. cuckoo's okay.

812
00:46:32.082 --> 00:46:34.835
Why don't you get over there
and settle down Carley for me?

813
00:46:35.002 --> 00:46:37.087
-Could you do that for me?
-Yes. sir.

814
00:46:37.254 --> 00:46:38.797
There you go.

815
00:46:40.048 --> 00:46:42.092
What began as a day
of hope and optimism...

816
00:46:42.259 --> 00:46:45.595
...for Ricky Bobby and his race team
has ended here in disappointment.

817
00:46:45.762 --> 00:46:47.014
There we go. boy.

818
00:46:47.180 --> 00:46:49.057
-I lost all muscle control.
-Yeah. you did.

819
00:46:49.224 --> 00:46:52.686
-He just lost his muscle control is all.
-I lost my muscle control.

820
00:46:53.395 --> 00:46:56.231
He's fine.
He just can't control the muscles.

821
00:47:05.741 --> 00:47:08.201
-Thanks for the lift. Hershell.
-Yeah. no problem.

822
00:47:14.041 --> 00:47:15.459
Jenga!

823
00:47:17.210 --> 00:47:18.712
I love you. Cal.

824
00:47:20.255 --> 00:47:22.549
-Good one. kiddo.
-What the hell's going on?

825
00:47:22.716 --> 00:47:24.843
Hey. Ricky. nice of you
to stop by for a visit.

826
00:47:25.010 --> 00:47:27.888
What do you mean. a visit?
This is my house.

827
00:47:28.055 --> 00:47:29.598
Baby...

828
00:47:29.765 --> 00:47:31.933
...shoot I'm so sorry.

829
00:47:32.100 --> 00:47:34.353
I really--
I didn't want it to be this way.

830
00:47:34.519 --> 00:47:36.938
Hey. what happened
to the family portrait?

831
00:47:37.647 --> 00:47:39.858
You just crudely pasted
your face over mine.

832
00:47:40.025 --> 00:47:41.943
We're getting married. Ricky.

833
00:47:42.110 --> 00:47:44.613
And we're getting matching
leprechaun tattoos.

834
00:47:44.780 --> 00:47:46.698
Isn't that cute?
With a little pot of gold.

835
00:47:46.865 --> 00:47:49.117
Is this some kind of joke?
You guys putting me on?

836
00:47:49.284 --> 00:47:53.372
I was gone three hours.
Dennit just fired me from the team.

837
00:47:53.997 --> 00:47:55.457
Ricky. you and I...

838
00:47:55.624 --> 00:47:59.169
...we both know that this marriage
has been over for a long. long time.

839
00:47:59.378 --> 00:48:02.422
No! I honestly did not know that!

840
00:48:02.589 --> 00:48:04.925
Ricky. I'm a driver's wife.

841
00:48:05.092 --> 00:48:07.803
I don't work. Okay?

842
00:48:07.969 --> 00:48:11.807
Wait. Hold on. Hold on. Just a second.
Let me make sure I got this straight.

843
00:48:12.432 --> 00:48:14.226
Are you asking me for a divorce?

844
00:48:14.393 --> 00:48:16.978
-Yay! Two Christmases!
-Yay! Two Christmases!

845
00:48:17.145 --> 00:48:19.022
Cal?

846
00:48:19.189 --> 00:48:21.066
How could you do this to me. man?

847
00:48:21.233 --> 00:48:24.861
Ricky. your marriage was
a hollow shell.

848
00:48:25.028 --> 00:48:26.738
It was a cruel Charade.

849
00:48:26.905 --> 00:48:28.990
She just gave me the 411
on the whole deal.

850
00:48:29.157 --> 00:48:32.577
And you know what else?
You never let me win one time.

851
00:48:32.744 --> 00:48:35.163
I thought we had a good thing going.
Shake and Bake.

852
00:48:35.330 --> 00:48:38.041
You're doing great.
You just keep it up. Keep it up.

853
00:48:38.208 --> 00:48:41.211
And Mr. Dennit told me
that it's my time now.

854
00:48:41.378 --> 00:48:43.505
-Oh. really?
-That Shake and Bake is dead.

855
00:48:43.672 --> 00:48:46.174
And we just came up
with a new nickname.

856
00:48:46.341 --> 00:48:48.844
-it's so good. it's so good.
-I got a new nickname.

857
00:48:49.052 --> 00:48:51.888
The Magic Man.
Now you see me...

858
00:48:52.764 --> 00:48:54.266
...now you don't.

859
00:48:54.433 --> 00:48:56.643
That is the stupidest nickname
I've ever heard.

860
00:48:56.810 --> 00:48:58.520
Is it. Ricky?

861
00:48:58.687 --> 00:49:00.981
Because I think
you wish you thought of it.

862
00:49:03.066 --> 00:49:05.569
All right. You got me.
That's an awesome nickname.

863
00:49:05.735 --> 00:49:09.364
Watch the mail for that invitation to the
wedding. because I want you there.

864
00:49:09.531 --> 00:49:10.782
-What'?!
-I know it...

865
00:49:10.949 --> 00:49:13.743
...that some bad stuff happened
just now. but in time--

866
00:49:13.910 --> 00:49:15.745
The wedding's not for
a couple of weeks.

867
00:49:15.912 --> 00:49:17.831
Why would I come
to your guys' wedding?

868
00:49:17.998 --> 00:49:20.000
--you're gonna get over it
and be my best man.

869
00:49:20.167 --> 00:49:21.585
I'm not gonna be your best man!

870
00:49:21.751 --> 00:49:23.712
Baby. he's not gonna come
to the wedding.

871
00:49:23.879 --> 00:49:28.008
Cal. do you realize the implications
of your actions right now?

872
00:49:28.175 --> 00:49:29.468
What's "implication" mean?

873
00:49:29.634 --> 00:49:31.094
We are no longer friends.

874
00:49:31.303 --> 00:49:33.972
-Why?
-What do you mean. "Why'?"

875
00:49:34.931 --> 00:49:36.266
You're wrecking my life!

876
00:49:36.433 --> 00:49:39.144
You just lost your wife.
You just lost your job.

877
00:49:39.311 --> 00:49:42.063
Don't throw out your best friend
because of your anger.

878
00:49:42.564 --> 00:49:45.692
-That's absolutely ridiculous. man.
-Ricky...

879
00:49:45.859 --> 00:49:50.822
...remember. the field mouse is fast.
but the owl sees at night.

880
00:49:54.576 --> 00:49:56.328
That's kind of creepy. ain't it?

881
00:49:59.915 --> 00:50:02.792
-Hey. Ricky. I'll call you tomorrow.
-Shut up.

882
00:50:02.959 --> 00:50:05.670
-Bye. kids. I'll see you next weekend.
-Bye.

883
00:50:10.258 --> 00:50:14.095
Ricky! Boys! Is everything all right?

884
00:50:14.304 --> 00:50:17.974
Mama. we got nowhere to go.
Carley and Cal took everything.

885
00:50:18.141 --> 00:50:20.143
Well. you're home now.
and you got your mama.

886
00:50:20.310 --> 00:50:21.520
Get in here. boys. Come on.

887
00:50:21.686 --> 00:50:24.439
Come on. Get in this house.

888
00:50:31.279 --> 00:50:33.490
Hey. Ricky. Are you on fire?

889
00:50:34.282 --> 00:50:37.619
-Nice denim shorts. dude.
-Hey. shut up. man.

890
00:50:50.173 --> 00:50:51.633
Hump me!

891
00:50:55.554 --> 00:50:57.472
Now. you watch yourself.

892
00:50:57.639 --> 00:51:00.976
Yes. sir. I'm sorry.
I promise it won't happen again.

893
00:51:07.732 --> 00:51:09.359
Hey. sorry. man.

894
00:51:11.903 --> 00:51:14.781
-Sorry. Sorry.
-Get out of the road!

895
00:51:14.948 --> 00:51:17.909
Hey. come on. man.
I'm on a bike. Relax.

896
00:51:18.076 --> 00:51:20.412
-Hey. shut up!
-Idiot!

897
00:51:24.332 --> 00:51:25.959
It's open.

898
00:51:28.003 --> 00:51:30.088
Hugalo's Pizza. We are pizza.

899
00:51:31.923 --> 00:51:35.010
-You are pizza?
-Yeah. we are pizza. I gotta say it.

900
00:51:37.387 --> 00:51:40.682
Either close the door or come in.
I got weed in here. cowboy.

901
00:51:46.646 --> 00:51:49.733
You got three pizzas that haven't
been eaten just sitting over there.

902
00:51:49.899 --> 00:51:52.694
I know. I've been calling them
all day trying to get you...

903
00:51:52.861 --> 00:51:55.238
...but they keep sending me
different delivery people.

904
00:51:55.405 --> 00:51:57.198
Trying to get me? Why?

905
00:51:57.365 --> 00:51:59.075
Because I'm your daddy. that's why.

906
00:52:00.702 --> 00:52:03.788
-What did you just say?
-I said. I'm your daddy.

907
00:52:03.955 --> 00:52:05.540
I'm Reese Bobby.

908
00:52:05.707 --> 00:52:10.545
Me and your mama did it in a Rustler
Steak House bathroom when I was 17.

909
00:52:10.712 --> 00:52:12.547
And then you showed up.

910
00:52:19.304 --> 00:52:21.222
Hey. son.

911
00:52:21.389 --> 00:52:24.726
-Son! Son. did this go good?
-No!

912
00:52:24.893 --> 00:52:27.854
-Seems to me like it went pretty good.
-You're not my dad.

913
00:52:28.021 --> 00:52:30.357
-It got e little heated. but ....
-Stop talking to me!

914
00:52:30.523 --> 00:52:33.652
Hey. is that a Huffy?
That's a nice-looking bike. boy.

915
00:52:33.818 --> 00:52:35.654
I can't believe it!

916
00:52:35.820 --> 00:52:38.990
I mean. he's been
blowing me off for 25 years...

917
00:52:39.157 --> 00:52:41.743
...and now he wants
to get to know me?

918
00:52:41.910 --> 00:52:43.787
How the hell did he even find me?

919
00:52:43.953 --> 00:52:45.288
I called him.

920
00:52:45.455 --> 00:52:48.416
Are you kidding me?
Mama. why did you go do that?

921
