01:20:21.234 --> 01:20:23.403
Guys. let's go win ourselves
a race. all right?

1376
01:20:23.570 --> 01:20:25.655
-There you go. Yeah!
-Right?

1377
01:20:25.822 --> 01:20:28.241
Let's get out there and win a race.

1378
01:20:42.422 --> 01:20:44.883
From West River. North Carolina...

1379
01:20:45.091 --> 01:20:48.303
...driver of the number 47
Old Spice car...

1380
01:20:48.470 --> 01:20:51.723
...Cal Naughton Jr.

1381
01:21:00.774 --> 01:21:02.609
Hey. Carley.

1382
01:21:02.776 --> 01:21:06.446
-Hey. Ricky.
-Carley! Hey. baby.

1383
01:21:08.323 --> 01:21:09.949
Baby.

1384
01:21:10.116 --> 01:21:12.118
Oh. hey. Ricky.

1385
01:21:12.285 --> 01:21:14.913
Hey. man.
We missed you at the wedding.

1386
01:21:15.080 --> 01:21:18.083
-You missed me at the wedding?
-Oh. man. it was so classy.

1387
01:21:18.249 --> 01:21:21.628
We had a Styx cover band
and a nacho fountain.

1388
01:21:21.795 --> 01:21:24.798
Check it. it was a nacho fountain
with six kinds of cheese on it.

1389
01:21:24.964 --> 01:21:28.259
-Liquid cheese? It cascaded down?
-Yeah.

1390
01:21:28.426 --> 01:21:30.553
-Are you serious?
-Amazing. Six different kinds.

1391
01:21:30.720 --> 01:21:32.305
Swiss. Havarti.
What was the other one?

1392
01:21:32.472 --> 01:21:33.556
-Gouda.
-Cheddar. Gouda.

1393
01:21:33.723 --> 01:21:35.683
That's the greatest thing
I ever heard of.

1394
01:21:35.850 --> 01:21:37.769
Bean buffet in front of it.
It was awesome.

1395
01:21:37.936 --> 01:21:41.231
Don't listen to him. And remember
one thing. he's the competition.

1396
01:21:41.398 --> 01:21:44.275
You're not very focused right now.
I need you to focus.

1397
01:21:44.442 --> 01:21:45.819
-Hey.
-What?

1398
01:21:45.985 --> 01:21:48.279
-I'm the Magic Man now. Okay?
-Yeah. I know.

1399
01:21:48.446 --> 01:21:51.449
So get ready for some tricks up
these sleeves. all right?

1400
01:21:51.616 --> 01:21:52.909
Watch your buns. pal.

1401
01:21:53.076 --> 01:21:55.870
Baby. that is real good talk.
Like we practiced last night.

1402
01:21:56.037 --> 01:21:58.498
I got something to tell you.
you mangy piece of trash.

1403
01:21:58.665 --> 01:22:01.334
-What?
-I'm sorry.

1404
01:22:03.461 --> 01:22:06.965
I took you for granted. Cal. and you
were a really good friend to me...

1405
01:22:07.173 --> 01:22:10.427
...and I never gave you your due.
It was my fault.

1406
01:22:11.553 --> 01:22:14.973
I'll tell you the truth.
I'm a little confused by your tactics.

1407
01:22:15.140 --> 01:22:17.976
-Tactics?
-Yeah. I'm gonna keep acting tough...

1408
01:22:18.143 --> 01:22:20.353
...until I figure it out. All right?

1409
01:22:21.104 --> 01:22:22.730
See you on the track.

1410
01:22:22.897 --> 01:22:25.316
-Come on. baby.
-I love you.

1411
01:22:25.483 --> 01:22:27.193
I love you too. Come on.

1412
01:22:27.360 --> 01:22:29.362
Abracadabra. homes.

1413
01:22:33.408 --> 01:22:36.202
Hi. Bill Weber. along with
Wally Dallenbach and Benny Parsons.

1414
01:22:36.369 --> 01:22:40.039
Thanks for having us. Today.
Talladega. NASCAR's biggest track...

1415
01:22:40.206 --> 01:22:42.041
...where the big concern
is the big wreck.

1416
01:22:42.208 --> 01:22:44.335
And it's not if it happens.
it's where and when.

1417
01:22:44.502 --> 01:22:47.672
We have a guy in the race today
that'll probably cause it. Ricky Bobby.

1418
01:22:47.839 --> 01:22:49.966
Starting in the rear of the field.
underfunded...

1419
01:22:50.133 --> 01:22:52.719
...and the last time we saw him.
he caused a big crash.

1420
01:22:52.886 --> 01:22:56.347
A lot of big stories and some
big questions here at Talladega.

1421
01:23:08.985 --> 01:23:11.362
All right. go get them.

1422
01:23:25.335 --> 01:23:27.378
You must decide. Ricky Bobby.

1423
01:23:27.545 --> 01:23:31.216
Is it foolish pride.
or is it greatness for you?

1424
01:23:39.349 --> 01:23:42.185
-Hey. Jarvis!
-Go ahead. Cal.

1425
01:23:42.352 --> 01:23:45.480
If you slept with
your best friend's wife...

1426
01:23:45.647 --> 01:23:49.359
-...why would he apologize to you?
-Yeah. I know. That's weird.

1427
01:23:49.526 --> 01:23:53.279
That's what I'm saying.
My head's all tied up like a pretzel.

1428
01:23:53.446 --> 01:23:55.114
I got a pretzel in my head.

1429
01:23:59.869 --> 01:24:01.329
-Ricky!
-Come on. Dad!

1430
01:24:28.231 --> 01:24:29.983
I've got some big investors
coming by.

1431
01:24:30.149 --> 01:24:32.026
These guys are
big-money power players.

1432
01:24:32.193 --> 01:24:35.572
If things go right. they could have us
owning half the cars in NASCAR.

1433
01:24:35.738 --> 01:24:37.532
So I want you--
No. I want you to behave.

1434
01:24:37.699 --> 01:24:38.992
-Oh. really?
-Quiet.

1435
01:24:39.158 --> 01:24:41.494
Should I not tell them
after 14 years of marriage...

1436
01:24:41.661 --> 01:24:43.705
...you're still afraid
to let me see you naked?

1437
01:24:43.871 --> 01:24:45.915
That's not a fear thing.
it's a trust thing.

1438
01:24:46.457 --> 01:24:49.460
Hey! I was wondering
where you guys got off to.

1439
01:24:49.627 --> 01:24:51.754
Baby. this is Ted Beamen
from Halliburton.

1440
01:24:51.921 --> 01:24:54.007
-Nice to meet you.
-Over here...

1441
01:24:54.173 --> 01:24:57.010
...is Dick Tangfield
from Dynacorp.

1442
01:24:57.176 --> 01:24:59.178
-Back there is ....
-You have beautiful teeth.

1443
01:24:59.345 --> 01:25:01.055
Yes. he does.
Get yourselves down there.

1444
01:25:01.222 --> 01:25:02.932
-Adorable.
-Make yourselves at home...

1445
01:25:03.099 --> 01:25:06.519
-...grab something to eat. over here...
-Sweetheart. sweetheart.

1446
01:25:06.686 --> 01:25:08.187
You're a sweetie pie.

1447
01:25:08.354 --> 01:25:11.190
She's very affectionate.
She suffered a recent loss--

1448
01:25:11.357 --> 01:25:12.692
You taste good too.

1449
01:25:12.859 --> 01:25:14.736
--so she's a little emotional.

1450
01:25:14.902 --> 01:25:16.279
Okay. that's fine.

1451
01:25:16.446 --> 01:25:19.240
Go ahead. find a seat.
Can we get these guys something?

1452
01:25:19.407 --> 01:25:22.702
Jean Girard started from the pole
and is out to a big lead.

1453
01:25:22.869 --> 01:25:25.204
As you know. Bill.
he's been doing that all year.

1454
01:25:28.833 --> 01:25:33.254
Where are you. Ricky Bobby?
Come face your destroyer!

1455
01:25:35.381 --> 01:25:37.008
Come on. baby! Yeah. that's it.

1456
01:25:37.175 --> 01:25:40.011
All right. Lucius.
Time to let the Cougar loose.

1457
01:25:42.430 --> 01:25:44.307
Here we go. boys.

1458
01:25:52.815 --> 01:25:54.984
Ricky. you've got Brian Wavecrest...

1459
01:25:55.193 --> 01:25:57.570
...the guy that replaced you
at Dennit. dead ahead.

1460
01:25:57.779 --> 01:26:00.531
Bobby working really hard to pass
the Wonder Bread car.

1461
01:26:00.698 --> 01:26:02.492
That's his old ride. of course.

1462
01:26:08.998 --> 01:26:11.459
We've passed the halfway mark
with Ricky Bobby...

1463
01:26:11.626 --> 01:26:14.671
...now three car lengths
behind the leader.

1464
01:26:14.879 --> 01:26:18.091
Maybe subconsciously
you slept with Ricky’s wife...

1465
01:26:18.257 --> 01:26:19.967
...as a way of getting back at him...

1466
01:26:20.134 --> 01:26:22.929
...for making you
come in second all those years.

1467
01:26:23.137 --> 01:26:27.350
I know one thing. Carley was definitely
unconscious every time we had sex.

1468
01:26:28.976 --> 01:26:31.187
Lucius. I got Cal Naughton
dead ahead of me.

1469
01:26:34.565 --> 01:26:37.360
Hey. Cal. you should pay attention.
I think he's passing you.

1470
01:26:37.527 --> 01:26:39.737
Is Ricky passing me
in my subconscious?

1471
01:26:39.904 --> 01:26:42.782
No. he's actually passing you.
That's happening right now.

1472
01:26:43.282 --> 01:26:46.202
Go. Ricky! Go!

1473
01:26:46.369 --> 01:26:48.913
Didn't Ricky Bobby used to
drive for you?

1474
01:26:49.080 --> 01:26:51.040
-Oh. yeah. yeah.
-He's doing quite well.

1475
01:26:51.207 --> 01:26:54.252
Oh. yeah. yeah. yeah. Richard!

1476
01:26:55.086 --> 01:26:57.547
Get Cal Naughton's crew chief
on the radio right away.

1477
01:26:59.340 --> 01:27:03.594
I believe you have some tickets waiting
for me. My name's Reese Bobby.

1478
01:27:03.761 --> 01:27:05.346
Reese Bobby.

1479
01:27:06.764 --> 01:27:10.226
Mister. these tickets have been waiting
for you for e long time.

1480
01:27:17.358 --> 01:27:19.694
Who needs two? I got tickets!

1481
01:27:19.861 --> 01:27:21.988
Tickets. right here. 60 bucks a pop.

1482
01:27:29.203 --> 01:27:33.583
All right. Girard. I found you.
Now let's see where this goes.

1483
01:27:33.750 --> 01:27:35.293
Bobby's gotten around Naughton...

1484
01:27:35.460 --> 01:27:39.046
...and now he's right behind Girard.
but Girard's gonna block the track.

1485
01:27:39.213 --> 01:27:41.299
Man. he's scary good.

1486
01:27:41.466 --> 01:27:43.634
Ah. Ricky Bobby.

1487
01:27:43.801 --> 01:27:48.389
Now we shall dance.
and yes. it will be a slow jam.

1488
01:27:54.604 --> 01:27:56.981
Damn it. Come on. man.

1489
01:27:59.859 --> 01:28:02.278
I was wrong about you.
Ricky Bobby.

1490
01:28:02.445 --> 01:28:04.906
You are not the one to defeat me.

1491
01:28:08.701 --> 01:28:10.077
I can't get around him. man.

1492
01:28:14.332 --> 01:28:16.751
You tell Cal Naughton
to take Ricky Bobby out.

1493
01:28:16.918 --> 01:28:20.963
Hey. Cal. listen. I hate to add
to your tremendous moral confusion...

1494
01:28:21.130 --> 01:28:22.590
...but I just heard from Dennit.

1495
01:28:22.757 --> 01:28:25.885
He said to take Ricky Bobby
out of the race or you're fired. buddy.

1496
01:28:26.052 --> 01:28:27.428
What are you talking about?

1497
01:28:27.595 --> 01:28:31.349
Tell him if he doesn't do it. he's done.
That's right. he'll be driving a tour bus.

1498
01:28:31.516 --> 01:28:35.978
Well. you tell Mr. Dennit that
Ricky Bobby is my best friend.

1499
01:28:36.145 --> 01:28:38.981
-And it's Shake and Bake time.
-Cal. I don't like the way...

1500
01:28:39.148 --> 01:28:42.610
-...you're talking out there.
-Damn the torpedoes!

1501
01:28:50.785 --> 01:28:54.997
Come on. man. slingshot it.
Slingshot. come on.

1502
01:28:55.164 --> 01:28:58.334
I can't believe it.
If it isn't Mike Honcho himself.

1503
01:28:58.501 --> 01:28:59.919
Shake and Bake. buddy!

1504
01:29:00.086 --> 01:29:02.004
Shake it before you bake it.

1505
01:29:02.880 --> 01:29:06.509
Here I come. Slingshot engaged.

1506
01:29:09.554 --> 01:29:11.180
Yeah!

1507
01:29:11.931 --> 01:29:13.516
I love you. Cal!

1508
01:29:13.683 --> 01:29:16.519
-What are you doing?
-Can't believe it. Now I've seen it all.

1509
01:29:16.686 --> 01:29:19.981
Cal Naughton from Dennit Racing
just helped a rival driver...

1510
01:29:20.147 --> 01:29:21.482
...pass a teammate.

1511
01:29:23.484 --> 01:29:27.738
Darrell. you tell Brian Wavecrest
to take out Cal Naughton right now.

1512
01:29:27.905 --> 01:29:30.366
Right now. you do it. You do it!

1513
01:29:30.992 --> 01:29:32.326
Yes. sir.

1514
01:29:39.917 --> 01:29:43.004
And the 26 car just ran Naughton
into the wall.

1515
01:29:49.010 --> 01:29:50.595
Oh. man.

1516
01:29:56.434 --> 01:29:58.311
Damn you. Wavecrest!

1517
01:30:01.939 --> 01:30:06.193
The entire field was in that wreck.
and we've only got six laps to go.

1518
01:30:06.360 --> 01:30:09.238
Only Ricky Bobby and Jean Girard
got away clean.

1519
01:30:11.782 --> 01:30:14.243
It's just Jean and Ricky.

1520
01:30:18.664 --> 01:30:23.252
And now the matador shall dance
with the blind shoemaker.

1521
01:30:25.338 --> 01:30:28.507
Race officials have completed
an extensive cleanup of the track.

1522
01:30:28.674 --> 01:30:30.217
We're ready to get back to racing.

1523
01:30:30.384 --> 01:30:33.846
The 200.000 fans are on their feet.
and the green flag is in the air.

1524
01:30:43.105 --> 01:30:45.691
Bobby and Girard are
dueling each other for the lead.

1525
01:30:45.858 --> 01:30:48.194
No one seems to have the edge.

1526
01:30:48.361 --> 01:30:50.488
Go. go. go! Come on. come on. go!

1527
01:30:50.655 --> 01:30:53.282
Ladies and gentlemen.
this is the final lap.

1528
01:30:56.535 --> 01:31:00.414
By the way. Ricky.
I watched the Highlander movie.

1529
01:31:00.581 --> 01:31:01.999
It was shit.

1530
01:31:03.834 --> 01:31:06.379
Hang on. baby Jesus.
this is gonna get bumpy.

1531
01:31:33.030 --> 01:31:35.074
I've seen a lot of big crashes
at Talladega...

1532
01:31:35.241 --> 01:31:37.326
...but this is the longest one
I've ever seen.

1533
01:31:37.493 --> 01:31:40.204
Let's take a quick commercial break
and we'll be right back.

1534
01:31:40.371 --> 01:31:42.415
Hungry for both steak and shrimp?

1535
01:31:50.131 --> 01:31:54.010
Welcome back to Talladega.
where the long one continues.

1536
01:32:01.267 --> 01:32:05.438
No. no! Jean Girard and Ricky Bobby
have wrecked in the last lap...

1537
01:32:05.604 --> 01:32:07.398
...on the straightaway.
What a shame.

1538
01:32:07.565 --> 01:32:09.233
Oh. God.

1539
01:32:10.443 --> 01:32:14.238
It looks like neither Girard or Bobby
will finish this race.

1540
01:32:14.405 --> 01:32:17.616
We'd like to thank you for joining us
for NBC's coverage of NASCAR.

1541
01:32:17.783 --> 01:32:20.870
Coming up next.
it's Ice Dancing to the Hits of Motown.

1542
01:32:40.431 --> 01:32:43.350
Wait a minute. there's something
going on on the track down there.

1543
01:32:43.517 --> 01:32:45.770
Oh. my God.
they're racing each other on foot.

1544
01:32:45.936 --> 01:32:47.354
These men will not quit.

1545
01:32:47.521 --> 01:32:49.648
Go! Go!

1546
01:32:52.151 --> 01:32:54.904
Ricky. Ricky. He's going.
he's going. he's going. Look!

1547
01:33:32.399 --> 01:33:34.110
He did it!

1548
01:33:40.741 --> 01:33:42.910
Well. I'll be damned.

1549
01:33:44.203 --> 01:33:46.372
Good for you. Ricky Bobby.

1550
01:33:52.211 --> 01:33:54.463
Yeah! Yeah!

1551
01:33:54.630 --> 01:33:56.006
Ricky Bobby wins!

1552
01:33:56.173 --> 01:33:58.759
You'll never see anything like that
in a hundred lifetimes.

1553
01:33:58.926 --> 01:34:02.555
It was completely illegal and in no way
will count. but that was something.

1554
01:34:02.721 --> 01:34:05.182
It was. That was really good.

1555
01:34:07.685 --> 01:34:11.272
Monsieur Bobby.
by defeating me today...

1556
01:34:11.438 --> 01:34:13.941
...you have set me free.

1557
01:34:14.108 --> 01:34:16.610
And for that. I thank you.

1558
01:34:18.612 --> 01:34:22.366
I will never shake your hand. ever.

1559
01:34:24.076 --> 01:34:26.412
But I will give you this.

1560
01:34:47.600 --> 01:34:52.438
Sir. you taste of America.

1561
01:34:53.689 --> 01:34:55.608
Thank you.

1562
01:35:00.654 --> 01:35:03.741
No. once was good.
Once was good.

1563
01:35:08.120 --> 01:35:11.040
Boy. that Halliburton.
Halliburton's taken off. haven't they?

1564
01:35:11.207 --> 01:35:12.625
Yeah. yeah. we're doing well.

1565
01:35:12.791 --> 01:35:15.586
Now there's some stock
I'd like to get my hands on.

1566
01:35:15.753 --> 01:35:17.796
Ladies and gentlemen.
NASCAR fans...

1567
01:35:17.963 --> 01:35:20.591
...your eyes on Talladega's
famed Victory Lane...

1568
01:35:20.758 --> 01:35:22.635
...as we get ready
for trophy time here...

1569
01:35:22.801 --> 01:35:25.971
...following an exciting running
of the Talladega 500.

1570
01:35:26.138 --> 01:35:28.474
First. a very brief explanation.

1571
01:35:28.641 --> 01:35:33.145
Because the drivers that finished
first and second got out of their cars...

1572
01:35:33.312 --> 01:35:35.814
...they have officially
been disqualified.

1573
01:35:35.981 --> 01:35:39.777
So now the winner. he was third.
he's now number one:

1574
01:35:40.402 --> 01:35:43.781
Cal Naughton Jr.!

1575
01:35:44.949 --> 01:35:46.659
Yeah. come on. guys!

1576
01:35:49.161 --> 01:35:52.206
-Give me that thing.
-Cal. you're number one!

1577
01:35:52.373 --> 01:35:54.959
I've been waiting a long time for you
to say my name. man.

1578
01:35:55.125 --> 01:35:58.337
I know it's a technicality.
but I tell you what...

1579
01:35:58.504 --> 01:36:01.757
...you try to take this away from me.
I'll sock you in the face.

1580
01:36:01.924 --> 01:36:03.759
Ricky.

1581
01:36:03.926 --> 01:36:05.636
Give me that thing.

1582
01:36:08.472 --> 01:36:11.684
I can't believe it. I can't believe it!

1583
01:36:12.309 --> 01:36:15.145
-Cal!
-Put me down.

1584
01:36:15.354 --> 01:36:16.981
I'm proud of you!

1585
01:36:17.147 --> 01:36:20.734
Get up here. man.
No. you come up here.

1586
01:36:20.901 --> 01:36:22.361
You come up here.

1587
01:36:25.531 --> 01:36:27.908
-Cal Naughton! Cal Naughton.
-Oh. my God.

1588
01:36:28.075 --> 01:36:31.036
For this to happen ....
Am I dead. man?

1589
01:36:31.203 --> 01:36:33.539
You won the Talladega 500.
all right?

1590
01:36:34.957 --> 01:36:36.542
I owe you an apology.

1591
01:36:36.959 --> 01:36:39.420
-Come on.
-Man. I'm sorry about Carley.

1592
01:36:39.586 --> 01:36:42.548
She walked straight up to me
and grabbed me in the crotch.

1593
01:36:42.715 --> 01:36:46.176
-it's like a tractor beam of hotness.
-I know.

1594
01:36:47.511 --> 01:36:49.430
Shake and Bake?

1595
01:36:50.764 --> 01:36:53.934
No. Never again.

1596
01:36:55.894 --> 01:37:00.316
You're right.
I was a total dick. man.

1597
01:37:00.482 --> 01:37:02.568
From now on...

1598
01:37:03.819 --> 01:37:05.946
...it's Magic Man...

1599
01:37:06.113 --> 01:37:07.698
...and El Diablo.

1600
01:37:08.657 --> 01:37:10.409
What's "Diablo" mean?

1601
01:37:10.576 --> 01:37:11.785
It's like. you know .... .

1602
01:37:11.952 --> 01:37:14.204
It's like Spanish for.
like. a fighting chicken.

1603
01:37:14.371 --> 01:37:15.789
-That's awesome.
